The paper deals with the use of convolutional neural networks for optical flow estimation, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of unlabelled data to augment the training dataset, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of the trained network for specific domains, which is related to robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM).
